<i>adverb</i>: 언제나 [언ː제나], 언제 [언ː제] <i>pronoun</i>: 언제 [언ː제] <br>
<ul>
<li><i>adverb</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>언제나 [언ː제나]</dt><br>
<dd>1. always; all the time</dd><br>
<dd>어느 때에나. 또는 때에 따라 달라지지 않고 변함없이.</dd><br>
<dd>Every time; invariably without changing with time.</dd><br>
<dd>2. when</dd><br>
<dd>어느 때가 되어야.</dd><br>
<dd>At what time.</dd><br>
<dd>3. at all times</dd><br>
<dd>아무 때에나.</dd><br>
<dd>At any time.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>언제 [언ː제]</dt><br>
<dd>1. when; at what time</dd><br>
<dd>알지 못하는 어느 때에.</dd><br>
<dd>At some time one does not know.</dd><br>
<dd>2. some time; someday</dd><br>
<dd>분명히 정해지지 않은 미래의 어느 때에.</dd><br>
<dd>At some time in the future that is not decided.</dd><br>
<dd>3. always; all the time</dd><br>
<dd>아무 때에. 아무 때나.</dd><br>
<dd>At any time; whenever.</dd><br>
</li>
<li><i>pronoun</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>언제 [언ː제]</dt><br>
<dd>1. when; what time</dd><br>
<dd>알지 못하는 어느 때.</dd><br>
<dd>Some time that one does not know.</dd><br>
<dd>2. once</dd><br>
<dd>과거의 어느 때.</dd><br>
<dd>The time of the past.</dd><br>
<dd>3. any time; always</dd><br>
<dd>특별히 정해지지 않은 어느 때.</dd><br>
<dd>Some indefinite time.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>